# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*test*

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env
charts/*/charts/
# Exception: bjw-template must carry its forked bjw-common library tarball
# in git. ArgoCD renders each consumer with `helm dependency build`, which
# does NOT recurse into a sub-dependency's own deps — so when it pulls
# bjw-template (file://), bjw-template's nested bjw-common must already be
# present or the render fails with "no template bjw-s.common.loader.init".
# (Other charts/*/charts/ deps are remote and rebuilt fine by ArgoCD.)
!charts/bjw-template/charts/
!charts/bjw-template/charts/*.tgz
*/*/values.schema.json
# **/secret.yaml


# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/

*/*/.cr-release-packages

.ideainventory/
.idea
.DS_Store

.opencode/package-lock.json

# Python (tools/dashboards/ + any future Python project)
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
.venv/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.pytest_cache/
*.egg-info/